===date:Thu Sep 11 19:36:13 2003
===message:I'm not sure American equality means each worker in every workplace should be treated the same.  Granted we don't want sweatshops like there used to be but this society is a capitalist society. As long as conditions are humane, they can be different depending on the individual company's philosophy and objectives.  Some companies will spend much on lavish offices and workplace settings and others will be in a stark utalitatian office and workplace.  Ever wonder how Sam Walton made his millions?  Frugality.  So, if workers don't like the conditions in one place (ie/ benefits, pay, environment) they have the freedom (another American ideal) to leave and seek employment elsewhere.  Competitive pay and benefits will be generated by the workforce exercising this right.  Unions are not necessarily the best way for workers to get better conditions etc.  Federal laws protect the worker from basic inequalities like equal # of rest rooms for women and men etc, but not to regulate pay beyond the minimum wage.  
=========yorg=========
