===message:I agree that Berkman and Goldman, as immigrants, felt this need to help the "underdog".  As you stated, they "had no intuition to try and solve things the legal way".  There was no method to their madness. They did not even have the support of the workingmen or their union. Apparently, both were misguided extreme idealists. It is interesting that after prison, Berkman toned his tune down quite a bit and seemed to live a much quieter life.  His death was not a he had written it should be, "a sacrifice on the alter of the people", rather a cowards way out.
